title: Lifecycle: opening quick open quickly enough on startup looses focus
body:
Steps to Reproduce:

1. start code
2. before editors restore bring up quick open
3. 🐛 editor steals focus from quick open

Suggested fix is to let editors that restore on startup not steal focus if focus was changed by the user.

title: Cannot use backspace or enter after first opening markdown file
body:
Issue Type: Bug When first opening a markdown file or changing the languague mode to markdown, the editor does not respond to the backspace and enter keys. title: Reopen last open workspace not quite working
body:
Issue Type: Bug It seems to me that opening the last open workspace when starting VSCode, doesn't work quite well. I oftenly have it end up opening a workspace that I haven't had open for a couple of days. It *may* be because I seldom exit VSCode manually. I always just shut down my pc at the end of the day. I know that shutting down the pc makes Windows send a different message to applications as compared to a normal application exit. So, that may have something to do with it. VSCode wouldn't be the first application to miss this message. Please note I'm not talking about workspace *files*. I don't use those. I just open the folder I need to work in and call that my workspace.
